'''史蒂夫·艾伯特'''（{{lang-en|Steve Alpert}}／{{lang-ja|スティーブ・アルパート}}，{{bd|1950年|4月19日}}），全名「史蒂芬·M·艾伯特」（Stephen M. Alpert<ref>[http://articles.latimes.com/1999/oct/24/entertainment/ca-25526 At The Head Of The Pack] {{Wayback|url=http://articles.latimes.com/1999/oct/24/entertainment/ca-25526 |date=20131218104941 }}. Los Angeles Times. 24 Oct 1999.</ref><ref>[http://www.nytimes.com/2003/02/07/movies/at-the-movies.html AT THE MOVIES] {{Wayback|url=http://www.nytimes.com/2003/02/07/movies/at-the-movies.html |date=20131221000151 }}. The New York Times. 7 Feb 2003.</ref>／{{lang|ja|スティーブン・アルパート}}），暱稱「小艾」（{{lang|ja|アルちゃん}}）<ref name="aruchang">{{lang|ja|[http://ghibli.jpn.org/report/aruchang/ 【風立ちぬ】カストルプ誕生の話]. ジブリのせかい. 2013-07-15.}}</ref>，是過去居住在日本[[東京都|東京都]]的美國娛樂主管，[[吉卜力工作室|吉卜力工作室]]的前董事。

==人物==
曾任職於[[華特迪士尼|華特迪士尼]]<ref>[http://herocomplex.latimes.com/movies/hayao-miyazaki-studio-ghibli-films-spirited-away-to-the-big-screen/#/0 Hayao Miyazaki: Studio Ghibli films spirited away to the big screen] {{Wayback|url=http://herocomplex.latimes.com/movies/hayao-miyazaki-studio-ghibli-films-spirited-away-to-the-big-screen/#/0 |date=20130912230047 }}. Los Angeles Times.  25 Jan 2012.</ref>，因迪士尼與吉卜力合作而自1996年10月起擔任董事，負責海外業務長達15年{{r|aruchang}}<ref>Japanamerica: How Japanese Pop Culture Has Invaded the U.S.   Roland Kelts - 2006  p196 "Ishikawa's focus on the creative side of the industry is reminiscent of the description by Steve Alpert from Studio Ghibli of Japan's artist-focused process, and of its pros and cons. But Ishikawa is not suggesting that the artists simply do what they ..</ref><ref>Jonathan Clements - Schoolgirl Milky Crisis: Adventures in the Anime and Manga Trade -2010 p43 "“My secret source was Studio Ghibli — Miyazaki's people. I would run things past a guy named Steve Alpert. But every now and then, when the facts were against us, we'd go with the poetry. There's this one moment with a little dragon ..."</ref><ref>The New Yorker - 第 80 卷 p169  2005 "But during my visit to the studio Steve Alpert, an American who heads Ghibli's overseas division, showed me around, and in an upstairs room I saw Miyazaki hanging out with a couple of animators. He had shown the completed "Howl's Moving ...</ref>。雖是美國人卻能說一口流利的日語。<ref name="notes">[http://www.visualhollywood.com/movies_2012/secret_world_arrietty/notes.pdf The Secret World of Arrietty Production Notes] {{Wayback|url=http://www.visualhollywood.com/movies_2012/secret_world_arrietty/notes.pdf |date=20131213135553 }}, 2012.  VisualHollywood.com.  Accessed 11 Aug 2013.</ref>

2011年底，由於母親生病緣故，不得不退休返美定居，並開始嘗試撰寫[[小說|小說]]。<ref name="VisualGuide"/>{{r|aruchang}}但仍繼續與吉卜力有著往來關係，如從事英文版電影的顧問{{r|notes}}、以及在2012年7月受邀為動畫《[[風起|風起]]》配音<ref name="VisualGuide"/>。

